is it mom's or dad's responsibility to discipline your children when i grow up it was always my dad's job to discipline us myself my sister and by two brothers it was he who gave us groundings no tv time and even spankings now when i have my own children i usually do the not so fun bits like disciplining them do you think it is the dad's job or is that just old fascioned values growing up my dad was always the disciplinarian while my mom was the leniant one therefore we always thought our dad was mean while our mom was really cool being married now with two children i realize that it has to be a job for both parents my husband and i both will sit down with our year old and have a talk about what she did wrong and then decide together what is a fitting punishment be it time out no tv etc some days when i'm fed up i'm a stay at home mom my husband relieves me and will discipline our daughter and some days i do it but for the most part we work on it together The Adventures of Pete & Pete Rocko's Modern Life Married... with Children Spanking Kodocha Timmy Turner Kim Possible: So the Drama Charmed Cindy Sheehan Thai royal and noble titles Fancy Crane Laura Schlessinger Punishment Parenting The Fairly OddParents Shaggy dog story Divorce Malcolm in the Middle Blankets (graphic novel) Corporal punishment Trouble (comic) The Life and Times of Juniper Lee Intelligence quotient Incest Doug Dexter's Laboratory Cartman Joins NAMBLA Grandview, U.S.A. Cow and Chicken Calvin and Hobbes Friends Mr. and Mrs. Turner Joseph Jackson Baby Blues Bro'Town Social rule About a Boy Full House Kevin and Kell Recurring South Park characters Kyle Broflovski Fat Man and Little Boy (Simpsons) Futurama (TV series - season 5) Once and Again Fathers' rights Garfield EastEnders Teamo Supremo Springfield Elementary School S.H.E John the Baptist Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Great Teacher Onizuka American Dad! Raisins (South Park episode) Futurama (TV series - season 2) James Dobson KaBlam! Cathy Eric Car